        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The float validator works as expected with numbers endind with ,x where x>0, but with ,0 (or ,00 ,000 so on) it fails. With the following diff on FloatTest.php the test fails:\r\n83c83\r\n<         $this->assertEquals(true, $this->validator->isValid('10,5'));\r\n---\r\n>         $this->assertEquals(true, $this->validator->isValid('10,0'));\r\n\r\nThat's because the following line 113 in Zend\\I18n\\Validator\\Float.php returns 10 and not 10.0\r\n        $parsedFloat = $format->parse($value, NumberFormatter::TYPE_DOUBLE);\r\n\r\nSo the comparison in the line 128\r\n        if (strval($parsedFloat) !== $valueFiltered) {\r\n\r\nfails because 10 !== 10.0\r\n"
        },
